  "response_text": "In a bright, home kitchen with wooden cabinets and soft daylight, an adult woman with long light-brown hair stands facing a young girl across a white kitchen island. The woman wears a loose blue short-sleeved button-up shirt and looks down toward the child with a calm, matter-of-fact expression. A large red Eggo logo briefly appears centered over her torso. The girl, who has long brown hair and wears a pink-and-magenta striped long-sleeved top, sits at the counter with her hands folded, looking up at the woman as if responding to breakfast choices.\n\nThe woman then holds up a yellow Eggo waffle box at the kitchen island, angled toward the girl. The girl turns toward it from her seat. The kitchen feels lived-in and domestic: a stove and microwave are visible behind them, utensils sit near the counter, and a plate or bowl of fruit is blurred in the foreground on the island.\n\nThe scene shifts to a middle-aged man with curly dark hair and a full beard, wearing a pale striped button-down shirt over a white undershirt. He stands in a yellow-walled room near a white door, staring forward with a serious, slightly suspicious expression. Over several moments, his eyes shift and his face remains tense and puzzled, as if he is reacting to something unexpected off-screen. He gradually moves out of view to the left, leaving the background softly blurred.\n\nA black-and-white dog with large upright ears and a bright blue collar sits in another part of the home, facing forward. Its mouth is open, giving the impression of an eager or excited reaction. Behind the dog is a wooden cabinet or dresser, a framed family photograph on the wall, and warm household decor, reinforcing that this is the same family home.\n\nThe commercial then focuses closely on the food. A golden-brown waffle sits on a plate with a square pat of butter melting on top. Amber syrup streams down over the waffle’s grid, pooling in the square pockets and dripping over the edge onto another waffle beneath it. The syrup continues to flow in glossy ribbons, emphasizing the crisp ridges and soft-looking interior.\n\nHands hold a waffle close to the viewer and begin pulling it apart. A yellow circular graphic appears on the left with red and black text reading “0% artificial colors or flavors,” and small white text below reads “*Homestyle Waffles.” As the waffle separates, its fluffy pale interior tears open between the crisp golden edges.\n\nBack at the kitchen table, the young girl holds a waffle with both hands and takes a bite. A white plate with another waffle sits in front of her, with a spoon nearby and a syrup container partly visible at the lower left. In the background on the counter, the yellow Eggo box is visible. The girl closes her eyes and leans back slightly, smiling with satisfaction as she chews.\n\nThe final image is a bright yellow product display. On the left, red text reads “L’Eggo my Eggo.” On the right sits a yellow Eggo Homestyle waffle box, showing a picture of a waffle with butter. The box includes visible claims such as “0% artificial” and “No high fructose corn syrup,” with the red Eggo logo large on the front.",
